Three traffic police officers attached to Kitale Police Station have been arrested by the Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission (EACC) for allegedly taking bribes. North Rift EACC Deputy Director Enoch Otiko said they arrested the three on Webuye-Kitale road while a fourth officer escaped. The three were identified as Philip Kemboi, Wyclif Wekesa and Eliud Cheruiyot. &quot;We have been receiving complaints from the public and we decided to mount a surveillance,&quot; said Otiko. He said they set up video cameras, which recorded the officers engaging in activities contrary to the traffic rules. &quot;The details of what we collected will remain confidential,&quot; he said.&nbsp; ALSO READ: Sh1b SGR payouts that made Swazuri and team go off the rails